===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} – two hands on a [[plowshare]]. The two hands are still visibile on top of the character ([[爪]] and [[彐]]), while the plowshare looks like a vertical hook in modern writing.

===Etymology===
; "to dispute; to fight; to contend; to strive"
: Cognate with {{cog|bo|འཛིང་བ||to quarrel; to contend; to fight}}, {{cog|my|စစ်||war}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). One can thus reconstruct {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*tseŋ}}.
; "to lack; to owe"
: {{rfe|zh}}

